British American Tobacco Kenya #ticker:BAT has reported a 3.39 per cent rise in net profit in the half year ended June, buoyed by higher sales and lower costs. The company made a net profit of Sh2 billion in the period compared to Sh1.94 billion a year earlier as sales rose 1.93 per cent to Sh17.4 billion. The Nairobi Securities Exchange-listed firm declared an interim dividend of Sh3.5 per share, same as for the previous year. The company says its sales rose due to incremental pricing and distribution expansion initiatives. READ: BAT spends Sh392m on second staff layoff READ: BAT protests more tobacco taxes   Firmâ€™s share price falls to three-year low after drop in annual profit and dividend.